solution: We see that $f(f(x)) = -\dfrac{1}{-\frac{1}{x}} = x$, therefore $f(f(f(f(f(6))))) = f(f(f(6))) = f(6) = \boxed{-\dfrac{1}{6}}.$

We have that

f(f(f(f(f(6))))) &= f(f(f(f(-\tfrac{1}{6})))) \\
&= f(f(f(6))) \\
&= f(f(-\tfrac{1}{6})) \\
&= f(6) \\
&= -\tfrac{1}{6}.
\end{align*}Therefore, $f(f(f(f(f(6))))) = \boxed{-\frac16}.$
